contentrichtext.text: {{Wiktionary|rana|Rana}} '''Rana''' may refer to: In '''education''': * [[Rana Institute of Higher Education]], Afghanistan In '''entertainment and sports''': * [[Rana (film)|''Rana'' (film)]], forthcoming Indian film * [[Moon (Middle-earth)]], the moon Rána in Tolkien's Middle-earth * [[Rana Daggubati]], Indian film actor * Rana, [[Pin (professional wrestling)#Rana]] In '''places''': * [[Rana, Norway]] * [[Rana, Burkina Faso]] * [[Rana Plaza]], the site of the [[2013 Savar building collapse]] In '''science''': * [[Rana (genus)]], a genus of frogs * Rana, traditional name for the star [[Delta Eridani]] * Royal Animal Nursing Auxiliaries an outdated term for a [[Paraveterinary workers|Paraveterinary worker]] In '''sociology''': * [[Rana (clan)]], a family (clan) among Jats/Rajputs/Khatris in South Asia * [[Rana (title)]], a variation on Raja, a South Asian (Hindi and other languages) princely title of royalty * [[Rana dynasty]], an influential family in Nepal since the 19th century * The medieval principality of Rana of the [[Rani (Slavic tribe)]] based on the isle of Rügen == See also == * [[Raná (disambiguation)]] {{Disambiguation}} [[Category:Rajput titles]]
